Hi,

The new user <%= @person.name %> just signed up and indicated that they are a member of the following projects and/or institutions:

"<%= @details %>"

If you know they are a genuine member of the <%= t('project').pluralize.downcase %> you can manage, please assign him/her to the <%= t('project').pluralize.downcase %> by:
- Go to <%= person_url(@person, :host=>@host) %>
- Choose 'Person Administration'
- At the bottom. you will see the list of <%= t('project').pluralize.downcase %> and institutions that you can assign this person to

If the institution does not exist, you can create the new institution. To do this:
- Go to Institutions tab
- Choose 'New Institution'
After the institution has been created successfully, you need to assign it to the <%= t('project').downcase %> that you manage, by:
- Select the <%= t('project').downcase %>
- Choose '<%= t('project') %> administration'
- You will see the list institutions that you can select to assign to this <%= t('project').downcase %>

If you need to contact the person, here are their details: <%= person_url(@person, :host=>@host) %>, whose email address is <%= @person.email %> .
